Raheem Sterling has hinted that his long-term future remains at Liverpool after revealing that he dreams of hearing Anfield sing his name.

Sterling is stalling on a new £100,000-a-week contract offer, although he insists it has nothing to do with money and he will reassess at the end of the season.

The 20-year-old, who has been linked with a number of Europe's top clubs, has now revealed that he'd love his very own chant from the Liverpool faithful.

